problem_prompt: Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in mathematics would. Find $|9i-12|\cdot |3+4i|$.
gpt_response:
We will first compute the absolute value of the complex number $9i-12$. We have

\[ |9i-12| = \sqrt{(0-(-12))^2 + (9-0)^2} = \sqrt{144 + 81} = \sqrt{225} = 15. \]

Next, we will compute the absolute value of the complex number $3+4i$. We have

\[ |3+4i| = \sqrt{(3-0)^2 + (4-0)^2} = \sqrt{9 + 16} = \sqrt{25} = 5. \]

Finally, we will multiply the absolute values of the two complex numbers:

\[ |9i-12|\cdot |3+4i| = 15\cdot 5 = \boxed{75}. \]
